Designing Interventions Addressing Structural Racism to Reduce Kidney Health Disparities: A Report from an NIDDK Workshop.
Participants identified six domains as key targets for interventions and future research: 1) apply an anti-racism lens, 2) promote structural interventions, 3) target multiple levels, 4) promote effective community and stakeholder engagement, 5) improve data collection, and 6) advance health equity through new healthcare models. There exists an urgent need for research to develop, implement and evaluate interventions that address the unjust systems, policies, and laws that generate and perpetuate inequities in kidney health.
