Self-reported health change in haemodialysis recipients modulates the effect of frailty upon mortality and hospital admissions: outcomes from a large prospective UK cohort.
We confirm the high burden of hospitalisation and mortality associated with haemodialysis patients regardless of frailty tool utilised and introduce the discriminatory ability of self-reported health to identify the most at-risk frail individuals.
